Restaurant critic and festival curator Leo Schofield said living in Tasmania was the unhappiest time of his life . 
 He said the government cut funding to a festival he was setting up by 25% . 
 The struggle for funding led him to develop acute depression . 
 He criticised locals for wanting to 'dig it up, chop it down, sell it to the Chinese'Spokesperson for state's Tourism Industry Council said his comments were 'blatant mistruths'